  },
  "dimension_notes": {
    "cross_module_architecture": {
      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/uploadsvc/service.go` defines shared package-level `CommandValidationError` values (`errOpenEndpointRequestRequired`, `errResetOpenEndpointPayload`, etc.) and mutates their `Action` fields in `ValidateCommand` before returning them.",
        "`ValidateCommand` can be called on command execution paths that are request-driven and therefore likely concurrent across callers, creating cross-goroutine shared mutable error state."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "confidence": "high",
      "issues_preventing_higher_score": "Fix the shared mutable error template pattern so validation errors are immutable per invocation; this is a core cross-module contract boundary issue that affects observability and safety under concurrency."
    },
    "high_level_elegance": {
      "evidence": [
        "Upload action contracts are split across `goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go` (action token + protocol metadata) and `goseg/uploadsvc/service.go` (dispatcher execution/operation table), with no explicit single source of truth linking the public protocol contract to executor semantics.",
        "The two tables are guarded only by runtime reconciliation in `newUploadDispatcher`, so action-contract integrity is enforced late rather than by a compile-time-safe contract boundary."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "issues_preventing_higher_score": "Consolidate action contract ownership so protocol descriptors and service dispatch execution metadata are generated/validated from the same contract definition to prevent future drift."
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "mutable_shared_validation_errors",
      "summary": "Package-level validation errors are reused and mutated, violating immutable contract boundaries under concurrent execution.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/uploadsvc/service.go",
        "README.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/uploadsvc/service.go` defines exported error values as package variables (`errOpenEndpointRequestRequired`, `errResetRequestRequired`, `errResetOpenEndpointPayload`, etc.) and mutates `.Action` in `ValidateCommand` before returning the same instance.",
        "The code path `Executor.Execute -> ValidateCommand` implies request-parallel handling; mutating a shared error object breaks error immutability and can leak/overwrite metadata between flows."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace shared error templates with per-call constructors (e.g., `return CommandValidationError{Action: cmd.Action, Problem: \"...\"}`) and remove all package-level mutable `CommandValidationError` variables.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "contract_error_mutability"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "high_level_elegance",
      "identifier": "split_upload_contract_ownership",
      "summary": "Upload action public metadata and execution semantics are maintained in separate modules without a single ownership boundary.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go",
        "goseg/uploadsvc/service.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go` defines supported action metadata (`uploadActionMetas`) and parsing boundaries.",
        "`goseg/uploadsvc/service.go` separately defines `uploadActionDescriptors` for execution behavior and operation text, and `newUploadDispatcher` only verifies alignment at runtime.",
        "No explicit shared contract type/state links metadata to dispatch binding, so a future contract change in one module risks partial updates and hidden drift."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a single upload action contract artifact (including protocol token, description, validation requirements, and dispatcher binding metadata) and generate/use it from both packages to keep ownership and change flow explicit.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "split_upload_contract_ownership"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Mutable package-level error-template values for request validation contracts.",
      "Split ownership of action contract surface across protocol and service tables without a shared explicit schema."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "mutable_shared_validation_errors",
      "split_upload_contract_ownership"
    ],
    "possible_false_positives": []
  }
}


